<h2 id="using-icons">Using icons</h2>

<p>Icons should only be used when there is a user need.</p>

<p>They should be clear, simple and accompanied by relevant text.</p>

<p>Icons can be used for:</p>
<ul>
  <li>alerts</li>
  <li>search</li>
  <li>print page</li>
  <li>social media</li>
  <li>general functionality <em>i.e. closing alerts</em></li>
</ul>

<p>Icons shouldnâ€™t be used:</p>
<ul>
  <li>to decorate content</li>
  <li>instead of an image</li>
  <li>to hide a function, such as a button</li>
</ul>

<p>Our Icons are provided by Fontawesome. Fontawesome code is using <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;</code>, but you can use also <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</code> instead, and we recommened that.</p>

